    helpText: 'Learning to pause and regulate emotions during heated moments is crucial for preventing relationship damage and creating space for productive conflict resolution. When you notice tension rising, implement a 20-minute break where each partner takes space to breathe deeply, identify their emotions, and return to the conversation calmer. This practical skill builds emotional self-awareness and prevents reactive responses that can escalate conflicts unnecessarily.'
